reviewText: If you love music, you will be delighted with this DVD.  The works of various composers with a Spanish theme make for a fantastic performance, by the Berlin Phillarmonic, Maestro Placido Domingo, TOP violinist Ruth Chen (whom I have had de pleasure of listening to since her first concerts atan age of 8 (?) with the London Symphony.  The Soprano sings beautifully as well.  There is a contemporary piece played by the Phylarmonic  by the name of Huapango, which is extremely good.  This is my humble opinion.
